  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You must be proficient with wind instruments to use these pipes.</p>\n<p>They have 3 charges. You can use an action to play them and expend 1 charge to create an eerie, spellbinding tune.</p>\n<p>Each creature within 30 feet of you that hears you play must succeed on a DC <strong>15 WIS Save</strong> or become @JournalEntry[tjg0x0jXlwvbdI9h]{Frightened} of you for 1 minute. If you wish, all creatures in the area that aren't hostile toward you automatically succeed on the saving throw.</p>\n<p>A creature that fails the saving throw can <strong>repeat it at the end of each of its turns</strong>, ending the effect on itself on a success. A creature that succeeds on its saving throw is immune to the effect of these pipes for 24 hours.</p>\n<p>The pipes <strong>regain 1d3 expended charges</strong> daily at dawn.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>FoundryVTT</strong>: Allowing no-hostile creatures to auto save is not automated.Â  Recharging this item at dawn is not automated.</p>",
